po6
------------------------------------------
This is a library that includes all the code I tend to carry from project to
project for wrapping POSIX APIs for C++.  Where possible, things are
implemented inline so that there is minimal to no cost above and beyond using
the good old C APIs.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.4-1
  libpo6-devel-0.8.0-1bl2
  libpo6_0-0.8.0-1bl2
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.45-1
  cygport-0.37.2-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/rescrv/po6

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/rescrv/po6/archive/refs/tags/releases/0.8.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack po6-0.8.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./po6-0.8.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/po6-0.8.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/po6-0.8.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libpo6_0-0.8.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libpo6-devel-0.8.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(po6)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/po6.README
  /usr/share/doc/po6/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/po6/README

(libpo6_0)
  /usr/bin/cygpo6-0.dll

(libpo6-devel)
  /usr/include/po6/errno.h
  /usr/include/po6/error.h
  /usr/include/po6/io/fd.h
  /usr/include/po6/io/mmap.h
  /usr/include/po6/net/hostname.h
  /usr/include/po6/net/ipaddr.h
  /usr/include/po6/net/location.h
  /usr/include/po6/net/socket.h
  /usr/include/po6/noncopyable.h
  /usr/include/po6/pathname.h
  /usr/include/po6/threads/barrier.h
  /usr/include/po6/threads/cond.h
  /usr/include/po6/threads/mutex.h
  /usr/include/po6/threads/rwlock.h
  /usr/include/po6/threads/thread.h
  /usr/lib/libpo6.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libpo6.pc

